

The spiral is the usual anticlockwise Ulam spiral with  

\[
1\text{ at }(0,0),\;2\text{ at }(1,0),\;3\text{ at }(1,1),\;4\text{ at }(0,1),\ldots
\]

For a point \((x,y)\) let  

\[
r=\max(|x|,|y|),\qquad M=(2r+1)^2 .
\]

The number at \((x,y)\) is  

\[
\begin{cases}
M-r+x, & y=-r\;( \text{bottom side})\\[2pt]
M-(3r+y), & x=-r\;( \text{left side})\\[2pt]
M-(5r+x), & y=r\;( \text{top side})\\[2pt]
M-(7r-y), & x=r\;( \text{right side, }y\neq -r) .
\end{cases}
\]

---

### Position of 2026
The largest odd square \(\le 2026\) is \(45^2=2025\); thus 2026 is the first number of the next layer.
Hence

\[
r=23,\qquad M=(2\cdot23+1)^2=47^2=2209,\qquad d=M-2026=183 .
\]

Because \(d\in[3\! \cdot\! 2r,4\! \cdot\! 2r-1]\) we are on the right side, giving

\[
2026\text{ at }(x,y)=(23,-22).
\]

---

### The eight neighbours

| neighbour \((x,y)\) | \(r\) | side | number |
|---------------------|------|------|--------|
| (22, –23) | 23 | bottom | \(2209-23+22=2208\) |
| (23, –23) | 23 | bottom | \(2209-23+23=2209\) |
| (24, –23) | 24 | right  | \(2401-7\cdot24+(-23)=2210\) |
| (22, –22) | 22 | bottom | \(2025-22+22=2025\) |
| (24, –22) | 24 | right  | \(2401-7\cdot24+(-22)=2211\) |
| (22, –21) | 22 | right  | \(2025-7\cdot22+(-21)=1850\) |
| (23, –21) | 23 | right  | \(2209-7\cdot23+(-21)=2027\) |
| (24, –21) | 24 | right  | \(2401-7\cdot24+(-21)=2212\) |

---

### Sum of the neighbours

\[
\begin{aligned}
S &= 2208+2209+2210+2025+2211+1850+2027+2212\\
  &= 11050+5902\\
  &= 16952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{16952}
\]
